nscript\" data-duration=\"291.09\">comment out print_r,</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"294.02\">and then we will echo</span><span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"297.01\">and it\'s our $characters array,</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"298.09\">then we need a pair of square brackets</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"300.09\">and all we do is we put the index in there.</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"304.01\">So we\'re looking for the second element,</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"306.01\">that\'s index one, not two, we\'re counting from zero,</span><span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"310.01\">so if we then display that, it gives us Ford Prefect.</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"314.08\">So that\'s how you store multiple values</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"317.02\">in an indexed array, and access them using the array index.</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"321.08\">To create an indexed array, you could use the array keyword,</span> <span class=\"transcript ga\" data-ga-action=\"click\" data-ga-label=\"toc-video-transcript\" data-duration=\"325.02\">with the values you want to store as a comma-separated list</span><span class=\"transcript ga\" data-g